headline: Supply-Chain Tech Firm Overhaul Raises $105 Million
summary: Supply-chain risk management company Overhaul raised $105 million as it seeks to capitalize on growing demand for freight tracking services, in part to combat cargo theft.  The Series C funding round was led by Springcoast Partners and Edison Partners, with additional debt financing from MidCap Financial.  Austin, Texas-based Overhaul will use the funding to invest in artificial-intelligence technology and make acquisitions.
